## ğŸŒ How to Create a Basic Server? ğŸš€

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Using CommonJS (require) ğŸ› ï¸:----


const { createServer } = require('node:http');

const hostname = '127.0.0.1';
const port = 3000;

const server = createServer((req, res) => {
  res.statusCode = 200;
  res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/plain');
  res.end('Hello World ğŸŒ');
});

server.listen(port, hostname, () => {
  console.log(`Server running at http://${hostname}:${port}/ ğŸš€`);
});



ğŸ” About require();-

âœ… require() is used to import modules in CommonJS.
âœ… setHeader() is used to set the content type (e.g., text/plain, text/html).
ğŸ›‘ If you change your code, you need to restart the server manually!

âœ… To auto-restart the server, install nodemon:

npm i --global nodemon

Now, changes will be updated automatically! ğŸ”„âœ¨
ğŸ› ï¸ Managing Node.js Versions

âœ… To switch between different Node.js versions, use Node Version Manager (NVM):

$ nvm use 16  # Use Node.js v16  
$ nvm use 14  # Use Node.js v14  
